					<dt class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-2330">
<span class="avatar"></span>
<span class="comment_num"><a href="#comment-2330" title="Permalink to this comment" rel="nofollow">6</a></span>
<span class="comment_author">Carol</span>
<span class="comment_time">January 22, 2013 at 7:05 pm</span>

					</dt>
					<dd class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
<div class="format_text" id="comment-body-2330">
<p>A foreign driver&#8217;s license usually only works for people that hold double citizenship or can afford to travel abroad, &#8220;pretend&#8221; to be a resident by establishing an address and then getting a DL. It&#8217;s not possible for most americans that have never left their state!</p>
<p>I used to have a Brazilian DL and it was awesome. Got pulled over a few times, the cops, confused, always would let me go. But I let it expire and it would cost me too much to go back to Brazil and go through the process of renewing it (it&#8217;s not straight forward).</p>
<p>Anyway, the way I did it was to rent a temporary cheap room in a house, pretending to be an international student (since I&#8217;m really from Brazil and have an accent). I got one of my credit cards to send the bill to this address and then asked to borrow an utility bill because I needed to renew my DL. I even slept a few nights on my fake room (and told the landlord I was sleeping on my boyfriends the other nights). I took both bills to the DMV (in WA) and my new DL (that is good for 5 years) show that address.</p>
<p>A lot of work and some money down, but my current address is still protected from my ex husband, stalkers and whoever else that might be curious to where I live!</p>
</div>
					</dd>
